 <!-- Plots the four-minimum [Himmelblau test surface](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Himmelblau%27s_function) $f(x, y) = (x^2 + y - 11)^2 + (x + y^2 - 7)^2$, a standard optimisation benchmark. -->
 <h3>Himmelblau's function</h3>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>f</var>
   (
   <var>x</var>
   ;
   <var>y</var>
   )  =  (
   <var>x</var>
   <sup>2</sup>
   +
   <var>y</var>
   − 11 )
   <sup>2</sup>
   +  (
   <var>x</var>
   +
   <var>y</var>
   <sup>2</sup>
   − 7 )
   <sup>2</sup>
  </span>
 </p>
